{"ts": "2026-06-08T23:48:29.760818+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Now I have all the information needed. Let me compile a clear summary.\n\n---\n\n## How to Install, Configure, and Deploy This React Firebase Starter\n\nThis repository is a **Create React App (CRA) custom template** (`cra-template-firebase-starter`) that comes with React, Firebase authentication (Google sign-in), React Router, Material UI, and GitHub Pages deployment out of the box.\n\n---\n\n### 1. Install (Scaffold a New Project)\n\nRun one of the following commands to create a new project using this template:\n\n```bash\nnpx create-react-app your-project-name --template firebase-starter\n```\n\nor with Yarn:\n\n```bash\nyarn create react-app your-project-name --template firebase-starter\n```\n\nThis pulls the template from npm (`cra-template-firebase-starter`) and generates a new CRA project with all dependencies pre-configured (React 18, Firebase 9, React Router 6, Material UI 5, and `gh-pages` for deployment).\n\n---\n\n### 2. Configure Firebase\n\n#### a. Create a Firebase project\n\n1. Go to the [Firebase Console](https://console.firebase.google.com/) and click **Add project**.\n2. Follow the steps to create the project.\n3. Click the **web icon** to register a web app and obtain your Firebase SDK config values.\n\n#### b. Set up environment variables\n\nCreate a **`.env`** file in the root of your project with your Firebase credentials. The template reads these variables from `src/config/firebase.config.js`:\n\n```\nREACT_APP_FirebaseApiKey=<your-api-key>\nREACT_APP_FirebaseAuthDomain=<your-project>.firebaseapp.com\nREACT_APP_FirebaseProjectId=<your-project-id>\nREACT_APP_FirebaseStorageBucket=<your-project>.appspot.com\nREACT_APP_FirebaseMessagingSenderId=<your-sender-id>\nREACT_APP_FirebaseAppId=<your-app-id>\n```\n\n> **Note:** The `.env` file is listed in `.gitignore`, so your secrets won't be committed to version control.\n\n#### c. Enable Google Sign-In\n\n1. In the Firebase Console, navigate to **Authentication → Get Started**.\n2. Under the **Sign-in method** tab, click **Google**.\n3. Toggle **Enable**, then click **Save**.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Deploy to GitHub Pages\n\nThe template uses the [`gh-pages`](https://github.com/tschaub/gh-pages) npm package and includes built-in scripts in `package.json`.\n\n#### a. Update the `homepage` field\n\nIn your `package.json`, change the `homepage` value to your actual GitHub Pages URL:\n\n```json\n\"homepage\": \"https://<your-github-username>.github.io/<your-repo-name>\"\n```\n\n#### b. Add your domain to Firebase OAuth redirect list\n\nIn the Firebase Console, go to **Authentication → Sign-in method**, and add your GitHub Pages domain (`<your-github-username>.github.io`) to the **Authorized domains** list.\n\n#### c. (Optional) Test the production build locally\n\n```bash\nnpm i -g serve\nnpm run build\nserve -s build\n```\n\n#### d. Deploy\n\n```bash\nnpm run deploy\n```\n\nThis runs the `predeploy` script (which builds the app) and then publishes the `build/` directory to the `gh-pages` branch of your repository. Your site will be live at the `homepage` URL you set.\n\n---\n\n### Quick Reference — Key Scripts (`package.json`)\n\n| Script | Command | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `start` | `react-scripts start` | Run dev server locally |\n| `build` | `react-scripts build` | Create production build |\n| `deploy` | `gh-pages -d build` | Deploy build to GitHub Pages |\n| `predeploy` | `npm run build` | Automatically runs before `deploy` |", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 842, "prompt_tokens": 9327, "total_tokens": 10169, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 24, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 8768, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cos